OL,3,CFishing boat should have given way
OL,4,Cbefore deadly collision, defendant says
OL,6,FAs the defence began presenting
OL,7,Fevidence, Mr Carr, who is from
OL,8,FSunderland, decided to take the stand
OL,9,Fand told the jury that he would have
OL,10,Fexpected the L'Ecume II fishing boat
OL,11,Fto give way to the ferry, in line with
OL,12,Fcollision avoidance regulations.
OL,14,FHe said he first noticed the vessel by
OL,15,Flooking through binoculars and turned
OL,16,Fthe ferry seven degrees to starboard
OL,17,Fat 5:24am.
