OL,3,CFishing boat should have given way
OL,4,Cbefore deadly collision, defendant says
OL,6,FMr Carr said he thought that the
OL,7,Ffishing vessel would alter course to
OL,8,Fstarboard, but when it was clear it
OL,9,Fwas not following regulations to give
OL,10,Fway or slow down, he changed course
OL,11,Fsignificantly on the ferry's autopilot
OL,12,Fat 5:34am to try and avoid it.
OL,14,FHe stated: "We'd made the large
OL,15,Falteration to starboard, they altered
OL,16,Fto port, and at that point I was
OL,17,Fshocked at what I was seeing and
OL,18,Fsounded the horn to try and alert
OL,19,FL'Ecume."
