OL,3,CFishing boat should have given way
OL,4,Cbefore deadly collision, defendant says
OL,6,FThe Judge, Commissioner Sir John
OL,7,FSaunders, asked Mr Carr if he thinks
OL,8,Fhe should have alerted the vessel
OL,9,Fearlier.
OL,11,FMr Carr responded: "With hindsight,
OL,12,Fmaybe yes."
OL,14,FHowever, he added: "I thought my
OL,15,Fstarboard alteration would've avoided
OL,16,Fcollision, had L'Ecume not altered to
OL,17,Fport.
