OL,3,CFishing boat should have given way
OL,4,Cbefore deadly collision, defendant says
OL,6,F"I was maintaining course and speed.
OL,7,FIf you alter early, you can confuse
OL,8,Fthe other vessel because collision
OL,9,Fregulations are in place for a reason,
OL,10,Fit removes second-guessing."
OL,12,FAfter the collision, Mr Carr described
OL,13,Fhow he felt "shellshocked".
OL,15,FHe explained: "I couldn't think
OL,16,Fclearly at all, I felt frozen.
OL,18,F"My main focus was trying to get a
OL,19,Ffocus on L'Ecume and whereabouts she
OL,20,Fwas.
