OL,3,CFishing boat should have given way
OL,4,Cbefore deadly collision, defendant says
OL,6,F"I ran to the starboard bridge wing
OL,7,Fand looked over to try and get a
OL,8,Fvisual of L'Ecume. There was no
OL,9,Fvisual."
OL,11,FWhilst giving evidence, Mr Carr
OL,12,Faddressed letting Mr Sevash-Zade go
OL,13,Ffor breakfast, which left him alone on
OL,14,Fthe command deck.
OL,16,FHe said it was a practice from the
OL,17,Fother captain on board to help get the
OL,18,Fship back on time if it was running
OL,19,Flate.
