OL,3,CFishing boat should have given way
OL,4,Cbefore deadly collision, defendant says
OL,6,FMr Carr explained: "The lookout's role
OL,7,Fin port was to assist discharge and
OL,8,Floading of the upper vehicle deck.
OL,10,F"If he had breakfast before arriving,
OL,11,Fit saved 15 to 20 minutes that he
OL,12,Fdidn't have to spend in the port and
OL,13,Fgave the other deck another pair of
OL,14,Fhands to get the ship back on time."
OL,16,FHe said he would not have let Mr
OL,17,FSevash-Zade leave if there was any
OL,18,Fcause for concern, but "in hindsight,
OL,19,FI can see it's not right and it's not
OL,20,Fgood practice, nor something I would
OL,21,Frepeat in the future."
